7. (Optional) Open a new terminal/tab and receive DLT logs via TCP:
	# Make sure dlt-daemon is started with TCP enabled (option -t)
	# In a new terminal/tab, SSH into the container and run:
	dlt-receive -a 127.0.0.1 -p 3490
	# You will see logs sent from dlt-example4 if dlt-daemon is running with TCP support.


# Ubuntu DLT Docker Usage

## SSH Access
- Default user: `root`, password: `1234`
- SSH port is mapped to 2223 (see docker-compose.yml)

Connect via:
    ssh root@localhost -p 2223

## Example workflow
1. Build and start container:
	docker compose up --build -d
2. SSH into container:
	ssh root@localhost -p 2223
	# Nếu không kết nối được:
	# - Kiểm tra container đã chạy: docker ps
	# - Kiểm tra port đã map đúng: docker-compose.yml phải có "2223:22"
	# - Kiểm tra SSH server trong container: docker exec -it ubuntu_dlt bash rồi service ssh status
	# - Kiểm tra log container: docker logs ubuntu_dlt
3. (Optional) Check SSH service inside container:
	service ssh status
	service ssh restart
4. Start DLT Daemon before running the example:
	ls -l /usr/local/bin/dlt-daemon           # Check if dlt-daemon is installed
	dlt-daemon &                              # Start DLT Daemon in background
	ps aux | grep dlt-daemon                  # Verify dlt-daemon is running
5. Run the dlt-example4 binary:
	ls -l /usr/src/myapp/build/dlt-example4   # Check if the binary exists
	cd /usr/src/myapp/build/                  # Go to build directory
	./dlt-example4                            # Run the example
6. View DLT logs after running the example:
	# By default, DLT Daemon outputs logs to stdout. You can redirect output to a file if needed:
	#   dlt-daemon > /tmp/dlt.log 2>&1 &
	#   tail -f /tmp/dlt.log
	# Or simply observe the output in the terminal where dlt-daemon is running.

## Rebuild container
	docker compose down
	docker compose up --build -d
